metadata.name: Risonanza #273
metadata.description:
This series unearths the unique and energetic rhythms found within simple repetitions. Using distinct minimalist components, the algorithm patterns, contorts, and intertwines geometries to reveal rich and vital maximalist compositions. The explorations of Risonanza revels in the quirks that emerge through this process, seemingly with spontaneity. They invite us to identify and savor the underlying simplicity of a common language that resides amidst all manners of imperfections, randomness, and intricate complexities we perceive around us.

Embodying the equilibrium between simplicity and intricacy, these works represent the dance between the innate harmony of existence and life's unknown paths. This balance of forces provides a simple and joyful invitation to attune to the energetic, complex, and singular harmonious essence of each work of art – an embodiment of the eternal resonance that courses through the universe.


—————

TENDER x whitekross
September 2023

Risonanza is Italian for Resonance, and is a generative art series created by Alessandro Fiore (AKA whitekross) in collaboration with Adam Berninger of Tender.

—————


Key commands:

1 = 2000x3000
2 = 4000x6000
3 = 6000x9000 (Dependent on your browser limitations, tested on Safari (Mac))
s = Save at current resolution

metadata.name: Orchard #333
metadata.description:
A natural media rendering of a fruit tree during one of the four seasons. Sometimes, you'll catch it at night - with lights strung on the tree!

The amount of color in spring and fall, snow in winter, fruit on and off the tree will all vary. There are four spring bloom palettes, four trunk colors, and seven types of fruit. 

Press ’s’ to save a screenshot. Image size is 1000x1000px
Press ’p’ to pause/resume.

To render a variation at a new size, open live view and append '?size=#' to the end of the URL. The new size may be from 100 to 3,000. This version will not be a 1:1 match to your edition but will have all of the same features.

metadata.name: Crowds #30
metadata.description:
Each iteration generates from roughly 100 to over 10.000 people depending on zoom and density. 

Other variations include color, hue range, saturation, brightness, outline color and thickness, each person's face, body, and the general mood of the crowd.

If you wish, you can check the console to see exactly how many people a crowd has in it.

This script can be run on windows of any resolution without any loss of quality.

metadata.name: Dahlia Pinnata 30 #188
metadata.description: 30-degree variations of a Dahlia Pinnata. The flower was 3D scanned, producing a 15 millions vertices point cloud. The point cloud was then simplified to 350k vertices, in order to be used here. This piece can still be a bit resource intensive. You can click/tap (or press 's') to stop the spinning, this should help if your device is struggling - @smallfly - fxhash genesis

metadata.name: Punk Haiku #8
metadata.description:
This NFT along with 70+ other artists artworks will be open to swap live during DPZ.NFT Art Bonanza Friday 8PM EST on Twitter.

More info here : https://dpznft.com/dpz-nft-art-bonanza

____

Haiku (俳句) is a type of short form poetry originally from Japan. Traditional haikus consist of 3 phrases that contain 17 syllables in a 5, 7, 5 pattern and a kigo : a seasonal or time reference. This generated artwork draws on the aesthetic of lo-fi punk  to create a series of unique poems, digitally animated to bring out the violence of the 80s counterculture in opposition to the sweet poetry of traditional haikus.

metadata.name: Mass study #7
metadata.description:
Study for skyscrapers maximum mass permitted by the 1916 New York Zoning Law. 
Model uses as input parameters like: lot size, max tower height, district class and area, surrounding streets etc. and generates skyscrapers with maximum permitted volume.
A few simple rules generate complex shapes and thousands of unique variations.

This project is also a tribute to Hugh Ferriss - pioneer architect exploring zoning rules, and NY - city shaped by zoning resolution.

Made with threejs

metadata.name: sandspiral II #152
metadata.description: This is a re-imagining of my new forms 04: sand spirals mint from hic et nunc in April '21. (https://hen.hicathon.xyz/objkt/68268 ). It has been altered to produce unique mints. There are 12 different random traits seeded from the operation hash, but only four are visible: primary hue, secondary hue, initial rotation, and line width. All values are equal likelihood, so there is no "rarity" per se; aesthetic value is the only trait that matters.
